    <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Andreas Linden (zolex) on 2012-09-02T13:33:02.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>when defining the route defaults as described here is does not work: <a href="http://packages.zendframework.com/docs/latest/manual/en/modules/zend.console.routes.html">http://packages.zendframework.com/docs/latest/…</a></p>

<p>'defaults' =&gt; array(
    'controller' =&gt; 'User\Profile',
    'action' =&gt; 'setpassword'
),</p>

<p>when providing the full classname for the controller it works:</p>

<p>'defaults' =&gt; array(
    'controller' =&gt; 'User\Controller\Profile',
    'action' =&gt; 'setpassword'
),</p>

        </div>
    </div>
        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Andreas Linden (zolex) on 2012-09-02T13:34:37.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>I think it would be best to define it in the same way as for http routes:</p>

<p>'defaults' =&gt; array(
    '<strong><em>NAMESPACE</em></strong>' =&gt; 'User\Controller',
    'controller' =&gt; 'Profile',
    'action' =&gt; 'setpassword',
),</p>

        </div>
    </div>
        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Jan Esser (esserj) on 2012-09-03T05:30:17.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>It seems that the way you call the controller is not in line with the documentation:
in the documentation they assume the controller 'Application/Index' is found under the Controller folder (src/Controller/Application/Index.php) in the current namespace
therefor specifying the full class path will in your case work. I do not believe this should be seen as a bug.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
